<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
1. 
<taxonomicName LSID="1A3A2D9E-EA58-564C-BE71-302D9709470F" authority="(F. Br.) G. W. Gillett, Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot. 66: 55. 1973." authorityName="(F. Br.) G. W. Gillett, Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot. 66: 55. 1973." class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyrtandra jonesii" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jonesii">Cyrtandra jonesii (F. Br.) G. W. Gillett, Univ. Calif. Publ. Bot. 66: 55. 1973.</taxonomicName>
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Cyrtandra jonesii (F. Br.) G. W. Gillett A Habit B Inflorescence C Bract D Calyx E Corolla F Flower, lateral view. Drawn from Wood 10744 (PTBG) and field photographs." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10494" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="basionym">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Basionym.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandroidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jonesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Cyrtandroidea jonesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F. Br., Bernice P. Bishop Mus. Bull. 130: 324. 1935.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
Marquesas Islands: Ua Huka: Hanay [Hane] Bay, 500 m, 16 November 1922, W. B. Jones 1712 (lectotype: BISH-501566!; designated by G. W. Gillett, Univ. Calif. Pub. Bot. 66: 55. 1973). H. St. John made a superfluous lectotypification (Phytologia 33: 422, 1976). A second syntype, Quayle 1243 (BISH) [now referred to 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="thibaultii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Cyrtandra thibaultii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] was mentioned as a &quot;second type sheet&quot; by Brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
Shrubs 2-6 m. Leaves opposite, borne on upper 2-5 nodes, leathery when fresh, drying chartaceous, broadly elliptic to broadly elliptic-oblanceolate, 26-40 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-25 cm, rugose, upper surface glossy, green, sparsely pubescent when young, especially along major veins, quickly glabrate, lower surface pale green, moderately ferruginous appressed pubescent, especially along major veins, quickly glabrate, margins irregularly serrate-dentate, apex broadly rounded, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
with an often long, acuminate tip, base broadly rounded, truncate or abruptly attenuate, petioles 2.5-7.0 cm long. Flowers in loose, open cymes 8-20 cm long, basally cauliflorouson the main stem, cymules 1-3 flowered, peduncles up to 30 mm long, ca. 3-4 mm in diameter, pedicels 0-1 mm, bracts rhombic, whitish brown, 18-20 mm, soon deciduous; calyx funnelform, whitish brown, plicate, 33-46 mm long, the lobes 10-20 mm long, unequal, triangular, sparsely minutely appressed pubescent, appearing glabrate, deciduous after anthesis; corolla white, tube funnelform, 40-50 mm long, slightly exceeding the calyx, lobes suborbicular, 8-15 mm long; style ca. 7 mm long, glabrous or with a few scattered hairs. Mature berry unknown, but young ones ovoid, ca. 10 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Marquesas Islands, endemic to Ua Huka, scattered in Hitikau area to Vaikivi summit and drainage, from 500 to 870 m. One collection (Mumford &amp; Adamson 561, BISH) made in 1929 is from Nuku Hiva, but it is possible that the locality on the label is incorrect and the plant was actually collected on Ua Huka, where Adamson was for four days in October 1929 (N. Evenhuis, pers. comm. May 2013).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jonesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Cyrtandra jonesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only in montane wet shrubland with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="B. C. Stone" authorityYear="1968" baseAuthorityName="Hombr. &amp; Jacquinot ex Decne." class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Freycinetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Pandanales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="impavida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Freycinetia impavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Gaudich. ex Hombr.) B. C. Stoneand 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tiliaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Hibiscus tiliaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. dominant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
IUCN Red List Category: Endangered EN B1ab (i,ii,iii) + 2 ab (i,ii,iii): B2: total area of occupancy less than 5000 km2 (ca. 423 km2). B1a, severely fragmented; B1b (i-iii), habitat continuing decline inferred. The suitable habitat for 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Cyrtandra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jonesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="38">
<pageBreakToken pageId="5" pageNumber="38" start="start">Cyrtandra</pageBreakToken>
jonesii
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Ua Huka (ca. 83 km2) and possibly on Nuku Hiva (ca. 340 km2), is restricted to mountain slopes and summits, indicated as an endangered environment that is threatened by human activity (deforestation and fire), feral animals, and invasive plants, reducing the extent of the forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Florence, J" journalOrPublisher="Allertonia" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="226 - 237" refId="B8" refString="Florence, J, Lorence, DH, 1997. Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands. Allertonia 7: 226 - 237" title="Introduction to the flora and vegetation of the Marquesas Islands." volume="7" year="1997">Florence and Lorence 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mueller-Dombois, D" journalOrPublisher="Springer, New York" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="444 - 460" refId="B14" refString="Mueller-Dombois, D, Fosberg, FR, 1998. Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands. Springer, New York: 444 - 460" title="Marquesas. Vegetation of the Tropical Pacific Islands." year="1998">Mueller-Dombois and Fosberg 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyer, J-Y" editor="Gillespie, RG" journalOrPublisher="University of California Press, Berkeley" pageId="24" pageNumber="57" pagination="332 - 338" refId="B13" refString="Meyer, J-Y, Salvat, B, 2009. French Polynesia, Biology. In: Gillespie, RG, Clague, DA, Eds., Encyclopedia of Islands. University of California Press, Berkeley: 332 - 338" title="French Polynesia, Biology." volumeTitle="Encyclopedia of Islands." year="2009">Meyer and Salvat 2009</bibRefCitation>
). If this species is restricted to only Ua Huka, then its conservation status would be CR.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
